Zeropipe
========

A simple way to share files over a local network.

Usage
=====

To send a file, just redirect the file to zeropipe's stdin, it will print a string that you will need to inform to the receiving side:

$ zeropipe < /path/to/file
<randomstring>

To receive the file, just call zeropipe passing $randomstring and redirecting zeropipe's stdout to a chosen file:

$ zeropipe $randomstring > /path/to/file

Dependencies
============
  - Python 3.4
  - pygobject
  - dbus-python
